      "content": "Yes, besides the compressor, other parts can also cause a humming or whining noise, especially when the fan is trying to start. A faulty or worn-out capacitor can lead to a humming or buzzing sound, similar to a motor issue. Additionally, a stuck or loose belt on the fan motor can also cause a similar noise. However, a capacitor issue would likely be more noticeable when the unit is on and the compressor is running, whereas a stuck belt might be more evident when the unit is not operating.",
